author: Byron Tau
title: Hillary Clinton Aide Meets With House Benghazi Panel
text:
WASHINGTON—One of Hillary Clinton’s top aides met with congressional investigators Friday, the latest interview in a long-running investigation into a terrorist attack on an American diplomatic facility in Benghazi, Libya.
Huma Abedin, a top aide to Mrs. Clinton while she was secretary of state who now serves on her 2016 presidential campaign, spoke in private with the House Select Committee on Benghazi.
